INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription Online publication and pioneering website that focused on technology, culture, and the internet, known for its innovative content and groundbreaking advertising.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Introduction' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'HotWired was an online magazine and pioneering web site that focused on technology, culture, and the internet. Launched in 1994, it was one of the first online publications to feature original content and to experiment with new forms of online advertising.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## History' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'HotWired was launched in 1994 by Wired Ventures, a media company that was founded by Louis Rossetto and Jane Metcalfe. The magazine was created as a spin-off of Wired magazine, an influential print publication that focused on digital culture and technology.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'HotWired was originally designed by the digital agency CKS Partners, which was known for its work on other groundbreaking web sites such as the LucasArts Entertainment Company web site and the Sega Channel.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'HotWired quickly established itself as a leading online publication, featuring original content from some of the most influential writers and thinkers of the period. The site also experimented with new forms of online advertising, including the iconic "banner ad" that became a ubiquitous feature of the internet in the years to come.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In addition to its innovative content and advertising, HotWired was also known for its bold design and experimental use of multimedia. The site featured interactive graphics, animations, and sound, and was one of the first web sites to feature streaming audio and video.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'HotWired published on a near-daily basis for several years, establishing itself as an influential voice in the emerging world of online media. The site also helped to establish Wired Ventures as a major force in the media landscape of the 1990s.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Legacy' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'HotWired had a significant impact on the development of online media and advertising, helping to establish the norms and conventions that would shape the internet in the years to come. The site''s bold design and innovative use of multimedia influenced countless other web sites and online publications, while its experimentation with new forms of online advertising helped to establish the internet as a major platform for commercial activity.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Today, HotWired is remembered as a pioneering publication that played a key role in the early years of the internet and helped to shape the digital culture of the 1990s. While the site is no longer online, its legacy continues to inspire and influence the world of online media and advertising.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- House & Garden Magazine
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'House & Garden', N'house-and-garden', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription Monthly publication focused on interior design, gardening, and lifestyle, known for its high-quality photography and authoritative editorial voice.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Introduction' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'House & Garden was a monthly magazine that focused on interior design, gardening, and lifestyle. Published by Condé Nast, the magazine was known for its high-quality photography, stylish layout, and authoritative editorial voice.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## History' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'House & Garden was first published in the United Kingdom in 1901 as a monthly magazine focused on architecture and interior design. The magazine quickly established itself as a leading voice in the world of design and expanded to cover gardening and lifestyle topics in later years.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In 1922, House & Garden launched a U.S. edition, which quickly became one of the most influential home and design publications in the country. The magazine featured some of the most stylish and inspiring interiors of the era, showcasing the work of leading designers and architects such as Frank Lloyd Wright and Elsie de Wolfe.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Throughout its history, House & Garden was known for its unique blend of content, which combined authoritative editorial coverage with stunning photography and innovative layout design. The magazine was also a platform for some of the most influential voices in interior design and gardening, with regular contributions from experts such as Edith Wharton, Gertrude Jekyll, and Vita Sackville-West.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In 2007, House & Garden ceased publication as a standalone magazine in the United States and United Kingdom. Its content was merged into sister publications Architectural Digest and Vogue, respectively.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Legacy' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Throughout its history, House & Garden was an influential voice in the world of interior design, gardening, and lifestyle. The magazine helped to shape popular tastes in home design and was a key platform for some of the most talented and innovative designers and architects of the day.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Today, House & Garden is remembered as a pioneering publication that helped to shape the world of home and design media. Its legacy continues to inspire and influence the world of interior design and gardening, and its archives remain an invaluable resource for anyone interested in the history of design and decorating.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

